<section class="gov-section sm">
  <div class="gov-container">
    <div class="gov-col one">
      <div class="gov-title-wrap">
        <span class="gov-eyebrow">[One operating model]</span>
        <h2 class="max-w-442">Local breakout where the mission requires it</h2>
        <div class="gov-badge-wrap md">
          <div class="gov-badge md">In-country routing</div>
          <div class="gov-badge md">Sovereignty</div>
          <div class="gov-badge md">Latency</div>
          <div class="gov-badge md">Consistent policy</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="gov-description">
        Not every deployment can route through a central location. Some missions
        require in-country breakout for regulatory, sovereignty, or latency
        reasons. EdgeConnect supports local packet gateways that preserve the
        same security policy and operational control while routing traffic
        closer to the point of need.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="gov-content-image-551">
      <img src="/assets/ec-one.png" alt="EdgeConnect Operating Model" />
    </div>
